  static uint32_t float32_bits(float value)
  {
      uint32_t bits;
      memcpy(&bits, &value, sizeof(bits));
      return bits;
  }

This function assumes:
1. sizeof(float) == sizeof(uint32_t) == 4
2. float uses IEEE 754 binary32 format

While these assumptions hold on virtually all modern embedded platforms (ARM, x86, RISC-V), they are not guaranteed by the C standard.

Add a static assertion:
  BUILD_ASSERT(sizeof(float) == sizeof(uint32_t), 'float must be 32-bit');

